[SN]TITLE[SN]
Conservative Party leadership: Who's backing who?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Conservative MPs have been revealing who they are backing in the race to take over from David Cameron as leader of the party - and prime minister.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Here is a list of candidates, in alphabetical order, and the names of those that have backed them publicly ahead of the second round of voting on Thursday.
The information is correct at the time of writing and will be updated as more MPs declare who they are supporting.
Liam Fox and Stephen Crabb both withdrew after the first round of voting and gave their support to Theresa May.
